---

User Roles

The system has three main users:

1. Passenger
2. Bajaj/Motorcycle Driver
3. Administrator

---

Passenger Application Features

Account

- Register using phone number
- Login
- Profile management

Ride Request

Passenger can:

- Automatically detect current location using GPS
- Select destination on map
- Choose vehicle type:
  - 🛺 Bajaj
  - 🛵 Motorcycle

The system should show:

- Estimated distance
- Estimated travel time
- Estimated price

Passenger can:

- Request Ride
- Cancel Ride
- Track Driver Live on Map
- Contact Driver
- View Driver Information

---

Driver Application Features

Simple Driver Registration

When a Bajaj or Motorcycle driver registers, collect only:

1. Full Name
2. Driver Profile Photo
3. Vehicle Plate Number
4. Identification Type:
   - National ID
   - NIRA Card
   - Passport
5. Identification Number
6. Phone Number

---

Driver Verification System

- New drivers have Pending status.
- Admin reviews driver information.
- Admin can Approve or Reject drivers.
- Approved drivers receive Verified Badge.
- Only verified drivers can receive ride requests.

---

Driver Features

After approval:

- Login to Driver App
- Online / Offline status
- Receive nearby ride requests
- Accept or reject requests
- View passenger location
- Navigate using Maps
- Start Trip
- Complete Trip
- View daily earnings
- View ride history
- Receive ratings

---

Passenger After Driver Acceptance

Display:

- Driver Name
- Driver Photo
- Vehicle Type
- Bajaj/Motorcycle Plate Number
- Driver Rating
- Live Location
- Estimated Arrival Time

---

Ride Process Flow

1. Passenger opens app.
2. GPS finds passenger location.
3. Passenger selects destination.
4. Passenger selects Bajaj or Motorcycle.
5. Passenger requests ride.
6. System finds nearby available drivers.
7. Drivers receive request.
8. First driver who accepts gets the ride.
9. Passenger tracks driver live.
10. Driver starts trip.
11. Driver completes trip.
12. Passenger pays.
13. Passenger rates driver.

